{
  "url": "https://www.qruise.com/industries/qc",
  "markdown": "[![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise.svg) ![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise.svg)](https://www.qruise.com/)\n[![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise.svg) ![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise_light.svg)](https://www.qruise.com/)\n  * Industries\n  * Products\n  * Resources\n  * News & Events\n  * Company\n  * [Contact](https://www.qruise.com/contact)\n  * [Docs](https://docs.qruise.com)\n\n\nQuantum computing\nAccelerate the development of your quantum device\n![1hour](https://www.qruise.com/qc/1hour.svg)\n< 1 hour\nfor system calibration of a 10-qubit QPU\n![30+ experiments](https://www.qruise.com/qc/30+experiments.svg)\n30+ experiments\nfor characterising and calibrating your QPU\n![digital twin 1](https://www.qruise.com/qc/digitaltwin1.svg) ![digital twin 2](https://www.qruise.com/qc/digitaltwin2.svg)\ndigital twin\ntechnology models your device perfectly\n![error budget](https://www.qruise.com/qc/errorbudget.svg)\nerror budget\nhighlights key sources of error\nWhat are the challenges in quantum computing?\nQuantum devices require constant recalibration to consistent performance and are highly sensitive to environmental noise, hardware imperfections, and the inherent instability of qubits.\n![wavey](https://www.qruise.com/qc/wavefunction.png)\n![circuit](https://www.qruise.com/qc/quantumcircuit.png)\nHow can Qruise help?\nQruise\u2019s advanced machine learning software streamlines calibration, characterisation, and optimisation, drastically accelerating quantum device development.\nPlatform independent\n![superconducting](https://www.qruise.com/qc/superconducting.svg)\nsuperconducting\n![rydberg-ion](https://www.qruise.com/qc/rydberg-ion.svg)\nRydberg atom\n![trapped-ion](https://www.qruise.com/qc/trapped-ion.svg)\ntrapped ion\n![nvcentres](https://www.qruise.com/qc/nvcentres.svg)\nNV centres\n![spinqubits](https://www.qruise.com/qc/spinqubits.svg)\nspin qubits\nRapid qubit bring-up with QruiseOS\nQruiseOS performs rapid, in-depth characterisation, calibration, and optimal control of quantum devices. With the option to choose between more than 30 pre-defined experiments or design your own, Qruise's rapid automated bring-up framework allows researchers to make more progress faster, accelerating the development of next generation quantum devices.\n![dashboard](https://www.qruise.com/qc/image9.png)\n[Discover QruiseOS](https://www.qruise.com/products/qruise-os)\nHigh-fidelity digital twins with QruiseML\nQruiseML uses advanced model learning to generate highly accurate digital twins of quantum devices. From arbitrary experimental data, QruiseML learns system parameters and iteratively reduces the statistical distance between the output of the digital twin and the real quantum device. By creating an error budget, QruiseML quantifies the sources of error, allowing you to fully understand which parameters are limiting fidelities.\n![qruise-ml](https://www.qruise.com/qruiseml/architecture.svg)\n[Dive into QruiseML](https://www.qruise.com/products/qruise-ml)\n[![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo-qruise-vertical.svg) ![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo-qruise-vertical.svg)](https://www.qruise.com/)\n  * [Company](https://www.qruise.com/company/story)\n  * [Jobs](https://qruise.jobs.personio.de/)\n  * [Blog](https://www.qruise.com/resources/blog)\n  * [Contact](https://www.qruise.com/contact)\n\n\n[](https://twitter.com/Qruise_ai) [](https://linkedin.com/company/qruise) [](https://www.youtube.com/@qruise_ai) [![bluesky profile](https://www.qruise.com/logo_bluesky.svg)](https://bsky.app/profile/qruise.bsky.social)\n\u00a9 Qruise GmbH 2026. All rights reserved\n  * [Privacy Policy](https://www.qruise.com/privacy)\n  * [Terms of Service](https://www.qruise.com/terms-and-conditions)\n  * [Imprint](https://www.qruise.com/imprint)\n\n\n![European Union flag](https://www.qruise.com/europe.svg)\nFunded by the European Union. Views and opinions expressed are however those of the author(s) only and do not necessarily reflect those of the European Union or the European Innovation Council and SMEs Execitve Agency (EISMEA). Neither the European Union nor the granting authority can be held responsible for them. Grant agreement No 101099538\n",
